entries.femaleVariant: NCPD! Open up!
Don't got no fuckin' warrant!
Barry! We know you're in there. We're here to help.
Congrats, Mendez, way to be a prick.
What's going on?
What's goin' on? I live right upstairs.
entries.maleVariant: Hey, what's going on? I live right upstairs.

entries.femaleVariant: So keep on livin' and stop mindin' other people's biz.
Sure thing.
We'll see.
Sure, why not. It's not like we're miles apart.
I dunno. Sounds too personal for me. I'm not the best shoulder to cry on.
Thanks. Just... be patient. Cops fallen on rough times can be... touchy.
Think about it, OK? Barry's a good guy, and a good cop. He doesn't deserve to end up alone.
We came here as colleagues – nothin' else. Haven't heard from you in a while. We're worried.
Noted! Now leave me alone!
Oh, what, so I'm the bad guy? I'm not the one who's holed up, playin' the attention whore.
He lost a friend. Can you blame him?
Mendez, hold on! It's his neighbor!
I'll see what I can do.
I'll consider it. Can't promise anything.
Is there anything I can do?
There anything I can do?
entries.maleVariant: Is there anything I can do?

entries.femaleVariant: Shouldn't be talking to cops.
This is a megatower. Spilling to badges'll get you pegged as a snitch.
He's a friend from the precinct. Left the force not long ago.
Maybe. You know Barry at all?
More or less. Struck up a convo once or twice.
This'll only take a sec. Do you know Barry?
He broke down after his best friend died. We're worried he'll do something stupid.
Relaaax, Petrova. Barry's got nerves o' steel – he's just a spiteful ol' bastard.
Cut the bullshit, just open up!
He's not the first or the last. It's called life.
Someone lose their mind again?
Someone in this tower go cuckoo again?
Could you check in on him when he's chilled down?
This is a private matter, so just move along.
Wait, she might know Barry.
Mendez...!
